reviews.review_text: nice matrix nice to hear the energy of the crowd AND the clean sbd! nice work!!

clean energetic good sounding show...a nice surprise not a *stellar* blow your mind kind of show but great sound combined with good vocals from Jerry and some inspired playing make this a surprisingly good stream.  A good jam for getting your stuff done.
woo hoo classic Bobby at the end of suger Mag! Great show!

alabama Getaway great opener

 jerr only seems to nail the song (rarely)
i dk no please someone explain to me why so many people go nuts over this stuff
Holy shit Mydland and Garcia at 3:50 in Wharf Rat....2 voices meant to harmonize!!!!

Cosmic tones it has been and always will be the cosmic tidal waves of tonal forces unleased by this ragtag band known as the Grateful Dead, that seems to cut thru reality and transcend the time space continum, catching us all in a whirlpool of joy and extacsy. Joy is the ears that hear.....
"If Music be the food of love.....play on!"

Great show I would love to have been there but..... Whats up with the 3 and a half minute encore???
I would have been pretty disappointed with that.
Other than that i have no complaints really good space> not fade away.

my response to penguin's (good) question... been a fan of this music since high school (early 1990s).   never caught the original dead lineup live, but i always loved the music.   i would've loved to have seen a show with Jerry, but unfort. i didn't.

recently, id been able to see two of the original members in their current tour, i felt very speacial feelings between crowd and band that i've never felt before in concert.   organized chaos?   for sure.   i felt to be part of a bigger picture and part of the music of what seemed to be timeless senses.   among the chaos, there was an extremely human element i felt, especially the need to feel physically close to the ones you love/you're with, since it's so chaotic.

THAT SAID, i took my wife to a following show, giving me tears thinking about it now, but i just wanted to hold her and be as phyically close to her as possible the whole time.  

that's what it's been for me.

1st time posting great stuff!  2nd show of a 3 night run.  2nd show of the tour.  Brent shines.  I really love his  B3 playing.  I knew some older heads in Chicago at one time and these shows were mythical to them.  something having to do with Phil being his usual boozed out self at the time and running late getting to the gig.  I don't know if there's any truth to it, just thought i'd add to the myth that is the GratefulDead.

Good, not Great I'm a much bigger fan of the following night's show.  However, being an '81 show, this one has some very good moments as well.  The most memorable part for me was the post-drums NFA>Wharf Rat.  

As they say, take what you need [of this show] and leave the rest :)

Just came from CA. To start tour. This was a great show. Called home to tell my mom i see her in 2 weeks. When the boys hit N.Y.C at MSG. She tolled me a girl name Peggy called. Well I fell in love with a girl name Peggy. I know it was love at the time we meet. Last time I saw her was SF 4 days before after a Jerry show at the Key Stone,SF. We said good bye. I had just spent the last 5 weeks with in Santa Cruz. And I really fell in love with her. So I called her and she was back in Boston. So we where to meet again. On her 19th birthday. We meet and off to the Boston show than to Hartford for her birthday 3/15/81. We have now been together for almost 31 years. With 2 great kid. Chris 25 and Jessie 23 and she making me a grandfather. Peggy I love you more than words can tell. The uptown was one of the best shows I have been to out of 258. Thank you the Grateful Dead for helping me find my LoveLight.My kids have been to shows and both love the Band. Hope the music keeps coming for many years to come. Thanks Richard.C

GREAT MATRIX-TIGHT BAND!!! This is a superb sounding matrix recording!! The band is "on" this evening!Very good song selection for 1981. Watch out for the abrupt cut in LOSER. Thanks to all involved for posting this gem!!!!!!!
Freind of the Devil There are many highlights in this treasure, having religous experience listening in my sunroom watching kids play, free...
Amazing '81 I love everything about '81. I think Brent felt totally at home. There was that special magic happening between he and Jerry. Clear for all to hear in FOTD.
great groove and punch on this night .
recording extraordinaire gotta give credit to the sound quality on this one!!!

Awesome recording... ...of an awesome show. 

Can only imagine what a good stereo system could do with this.

5 stars, no hesitation.
makes me want to get up and boogie... what a grateful listen. excellent quality. so glad i got to hear this!!

NFA>Wharf Rat The second set is outstanding. Quality audio is also a huge plus.
decent leads Scarlet Begonias>Fire On The Mountain from the Uptown is very fine.

9-2-1978 fire chris phillips

9-2-1978 You must be kidding yourself Donna ruined so many shows woth her lame singing. Lets be real when you listen to the tapes from that error it wasn't pretty. The boys later admitted it was a mistake to bring her on.
naysay no more nice clean sound.  gotta love a good "it must have been the roses"
wow - nice show Really enjoyed this tape. Thanks.
GREAT 2nd set I have never heard of this set that was sooooooooooo cool
eyes is a bit "too" fast its so fast they "skip" some words
The good and forgotten 80's Put your eyes on these one, it has an absolutely superb sound and a good song selection. The 80's Grateful Dead is my favorite.

Hope he has the sense to run... Here you have what becomes the standard formula for most shows in the 80's (without 99% of the flubs that become common as the decade goes on)
Sure wish they had kept Alabama in the rotation with more regularity it was such a rockin tune and gave Bobby a running start. 
A first set that builds in intensity (And only Jerry could build intensity with a ballad) includes a rare Minglewood set closer. 
A classic Scarlet>Fire>Est>Eyes
Steady drums and a pretty trippy space with like Elephants or whales or something?
NFA> Wharf> Sugar Mag (Got weary of NFA to close shows but like it here coming out of space.
Also fun to open a 2nd set)
Dang BRENT does have some out there backing vocals during Wharf Rat!
There is at least one complaint from a reviewer about the 3 minute encore but it's Don't Ease IMO-I would have traded a Baby Blue for a Don't Ease every once in a while.
Great listen GREAT show! I have a soft spot for 1981 cuz i cut my teeth on "Dead Set"! This is a great show with a little of everything. Some ballads, some rockers, and everyone shines a little.

My Last Dead Concert This is a decent recording of a very representative show from the early 80's. Also the last time I would see the Dead after attending just a few 70's era shows. I was never a Fan Boy even tho I collected their albums, and I tend to judge them very critically compared to other bands such as Allman Brothers Band, etc. I prefer tight, well performed shows just out of respect for the music and the fans who pay cold hard cash to attend concerts but what the hell, this is the Dead and they like it loose sometimes LOL. But this is a pretty good show compared to others I have seen. Never knew what the fuss was about over Donna ( I liked her) and it was Brent whose raspy vocals I utterly loathed! LOL

Holy Smokes Houston we have a problem I have not listened to this cover to cover yet but I can tell you this was not a good night for Jerry.  Alabama is bad and it stays that way. The first set was not meant to end with Minglewood something was wrong with Jerry.  Scarlet Fire is really bad.  There is a line between artistry and improvisation/dissonance and bad musicianship.  This crosses that line.  2 stars only for sound quality.

great sound! Really digging this show thanks to this AMAZING sounding matrix.  I had been previously listening to the sbd on the archive and then I decided to check out other sources since it felt too vocal heavy and had no "vibe."  I heard the aud that this matrix sourced and that felt kind of distant.  But the sound of this matrix blew me away!  This recording sounds as good as if not better than the bulk of the stuff from the vault that's officially released.  On the playing front, it's a great show.  Not without it's share of slight missteps and forgotten lyrics but the Scarlet > Fire and Estimated > Eyes were both nice jams!
Awesome Sound Great Matrix. Fantastic show!!!!!

Thank you! Thanks Chris for this amazing Matrix. I realize there are a few flubs on Jers vocals but the playing was excellent all three nights, this being my favorite. Sound is spot on 👌🏼 this is the one for this uptown run.
